that grows around Mt. Takao.

641
01:09:03,873 --> 01:09:07,332
You can see them
in May and June.

642
01:09:07,477 --> 01:09:10,674
I just added these on a whim.
But no one notices them.

643
01:09:18,588 --> 01:09:24,584
<i>0ga's orchids are the product of
attention to detail, a playful mind...</i>

644
01:09:24,994 --> 01:09:29,295
<i>...and a deep attachment
to the natural world.</i>

645
01:09:45,481 --> 01:09:52,444
<i>These little flowers are the work
of a quintessential image artisan.</i>

646
01:09:53,289 --> 01:09:57,624
What I try to do
is create backgrounds...

647
01:09:57,994 --> 01:10:02,989
...that do justice
to the actual setting.

648
01:10:05,068 --> 01:10:07,002
That includes natural phenomena...

649
01:10:07,236 --> 01:10:11,104
...such as the wind blowing
or snow falling.

650
01:10:11,841 --> 01:10:17,541
I want my backgrounds
to encompass all these things.

651
01:11:29,285 --> 01:11:32,687
<i>Kazuo Oga,
Studio Ghibli's image artisan.</i>

652
01:11:36,425 --> 01:11:37,915
<i>Oga has said...</i>

653
01:11:38,161 --> 01:11:43,099
<i>”There are no fixed colors
for plants or natural scenery.</i> ”

654
01:11:43,966 --> 01:11:46,492
<i>In animation backgrounds
yet to come...</i>

655
01:11:46,736 --> 01:11:50,502
<i>...who knows what colors
Kazuo Oga will discover?</i>

